> ----- Original Message ----
> From: Andy McKinley <airhedz(-at-)gmail.com>
> To: type2(-at-)type2.com
> Sent: Thu, March 4, 2010 3:39:29 PM
> Subject: [T2] tires - wheel size tangent
>
> So much has been written about tires on this list. I think that's why the
> archives are broken.
>
> See: http://tinyurl.com/ydsscjo
>
> I, too, finally gave up looking for any good mud and snow tires in 14".
> Yes,
> you can get the hankooks or vancos, but they are basically street tread.
> Yes, I know the hankooks are "rated"M+S. I used to run the Bridgestone
> Dueller AT's, but they quit making them in 14".
>
> I hade these 15x6.5" rims made from original centers at Stockton Wheel in
> Stockton, CA. I don't recall the offset, but I'll look it up if anyone is
> interested enough to pmail me.
>
> I have absolutely no problems with this setup. I don't have the fender
> clearance issues that are advertised by the vendor of the 15x7" rims. The
> only clearance issue I do have is a slight rub of the tread on the bumped
> out area as shown in the last picture, and it only happens when the wheel
> is
> turned fully to one side and the suspension is compressed. Obviously, a
> shorter profile tire would work fine.
>
> These tires are a good bit taller than the stock spec tires. My speedo
> reads
> a little closer to actual now, as verified via onboard GPS. The 79 fuel
> injection/electronic ignition limits the revs. so my top speed has
> increased
> (to what I don't yet know, but it's more than 94mph. Yes, it was downhill).
> The decrease in "pull" is hardly noticeable. Ground clearance has
> increased,
> and these tires will roll over a curb or parking block without hesitation.
>
> I have had correct reinforced tires, passenger car tires, correct LT tires
> and now these 15" LT tires on various vans over the years. The passenger
> car
> tires are definitely a hazard. The handling quality of the LT and
> reinforced
> tires are the same. Tire quality and good shocks make more difference,
> IMHO.
> I have the Koni shocks on all for corners, adjusted to the mid setting. The
> handling and braking is, quite frankly, amazing.
>
> From the horse's mouth. I've got it, and it works.
>
> Andy
